This paper discusses the unintended consequences of machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper specifically focuses on the downstream harms caused by machine learning algorithms. The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the potential negative impacts of AI on society. The third likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper addresses the ethical and social implications of machine learning. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper discusses the potential for machine learning algorithms to cause harm to certain groups. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper discusses the impact of machine learning on different populations and data generation processes.
